
Passage: The insistent drumming of the rain on the corrugated iron roof was a familiar lullaby in the village. Outside, the world was a blur of green and grey, the foliage dripping with moisture. Inside, Mama hummed a tune as she stirred the steaming pot of yam porridge, its aroma mingling with the damp earth smell wafting in from the open doorway. Papa sat by the dying embers, sharpening his cutlass, his silhouette a stoic presence against the dim light.','[{"text": "To describe the challenges of rural life.", "label": "A"}, {"text": "To evoke a sense of peace and domesticity.", "label": "B"}, {"text": "To highlight the importance of family bonds.", "label": "C"}, {"text": "To lament the lack of modern amenities.", "label": "D"}]'::jsonb,'B','The passage uses descriptive language to create an atmosphere of warmth, comfort, and routine within a rural home, suggesting a focus on peace and domesticity.',2016),((SELECT id FROM public.subjects WHERE name='English Language'),'jamb'::exam_type,'objective'::question_format,'easy'::difficulty_level,'Lexis & Structure','Complete the sentence with the most appropriate option: Despite his wealth, he lives a very ________ life.','[{"text": "lavish", "label": "A"}, {"text": "frugal", "label": "B"}, {"text": "extravagant", "label": "C"}, {"text": "ostentatious", "label": "D"}]'::jsonb,'B','The word ''Despite'' indicates a contrast. If he has wealth, but lives ''despite'' it, he must live a simple or thrifty life. ''Frugal'' means economical and thrifty.',2023),((SELECT id FROM public.subjects WHERE name='English Language'),'jamb'::exam_type,'objective'::question_format,'hard'::difficulty_level,'Oral English','Which of the following words is pronounced with a silent ''b''?','[{"text": "bombard", "label": "A"}, {"text": "limb", "label": "B"}, {"text": "number", "label": "C"}, {"text": "obtain", "label": "D"}]'::jsonb,'B','In ''limb'', the ''b'' is silent. In ''bombard'', ''number'', and ''obtain'', the ''b'' sound is pronounced.',2015),((SELECT id FROM public.subjects WHERE name='English Language'),'jamb'::exam_type,'objective'::question_format,'medium'::difficulty_level,'Comprehension','From the passage, what can be inferred about the family''s financial status?

Passage: The insistent drumming of the rain on the corrugated iron roof was a familiar lullaby in the village. Outside, the world was a blur of green and grey, the foliage dripping with moisture. Inside, Mama hummed a tune as she stirred the steaming pot of yam porridge, its aroma mingling with the damp earth smell wafting in from the open doorway. Papa sat by the dying embers, sharpening his cutlass, his silhouette a stoic presence against the dim light.','[{"text": "They are affluent.", "label": "A"}, {"text": "They are struggling financially.", "label": "B"}, {"text": "They are self-sufficient and comfortable.", "label": "C"}, {"text": "Their financial status cannot be determined.", "label": "D"}]'::jsonb,'D','The passage describes their living conditions and daily activities but provides no direct or indirect information about their monetary wealth or financial standing.',2020);
